######################################################

QUICK-START
***********
To create the files required by Flame-Master, do the
following:

***********************************************************************************************
> CreateBineFile -i Stanfordv12-therm-FM.dat -o Stanfordv12-thermo.bin
> ScanMan -i Stanfordv12-mech-no-Argon-FM.mech -t Stanfordv12-thermo.bin -S &> Stanfordv12.out
***********************************************************************************************



MORE EXPLANATION
****************

The original version of the mechanism has the ChemKin
format and does not contain any transport properties.

This short tutorial explains how to create a Flame-
Master format input file.


FILES
*****

* Stanfordv12-****-CK.dat: 
  Original files from D. Davidson (only for reference).

* Stanfordv12-therm-CK_modified.dat: 
  Same as original file but without header so that it 
  can be read by the ChemKin interpreter in the Flame-
  Master release (only for reference).

* species.trans:
  Transport data for species (required to create the
  next file combining thermo and transport data)
  (only for completeness).

* Stanfordv12-therm-FM.dat:
  New combination of thermo and transport file needed
  by CreateBinFile from Flame-Master and created by
  the tools in CK2FMReinh from Flame-Master.

* Stanfordv12-mech-no-Argon-FM.mech:
  New mechanism in Flame-Master format (mechanism with
  no Argon) that is required by ScanMan and created by
  the tools in CK2FMReinh from Flame-Master.


Now, to use FlameMaster, you need the following files
(they have already been created):
* Stanfordv12-therm-FM.dat
* Stanfordv12-mech-no-Argon-FM.mech

Do the following:
> CreateBineFile -i Stanfordv12-therm-FM.dat -o Stanfordv12-thermo.bin
> ScanMan -i Stanfordv12-mech-no-Argon-FM.mech -t Stanfordv12-thermo.bin -S &> Stanfordv12.out

You might have to comment out the line in the file
Stanfordv12-mech-no-Argon-FM.mech (already done here)
#let M = 1.0[OTHER].
and rerun ScanMan (see Readme file of ScanMan).

So, now you have the 2 files you need to run FlameMaster:
* Stanfordv12-thermo.bin
* Stanfordv12-mech-no-Argon-FM.pre